{"body": "Well for me, often times when I am testing a model, I want to isolate some particular behavior, and if there are callbacks along the way of what I am testing then it quickly can become a bit of a pain.  I will then have to have my test stub out the methods that are getting triggered via callbacks, and that makes my tests less clear, and more brittle.\r\n\r\nBeing able to turn off callbacks is a nice convenience, and doesn't have to indicate \"abuse\"...", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3877343", "created_at": "2012-02-08T22:08:30Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4885#issuecomment-3877343", "updated_at": "2012-02-08T22:08:30Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4885, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/patrick99e99", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/648553f5c693d93c9ea2e042857ad22c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F25b6a534a8c88b8e73fe7b865fd36bde.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/received_events", "gravatar_id": "648553f5c693d93c9ea2e042857ad22c", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "patrick99e99", "type": "User", "id": 28946, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/patrick99e99/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381ff5bd3543c15100e865"}, "id": 3877343, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4885"}
